This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump at a ceremony welcoming General Mark Milley as the new Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff. The President praised General Milley's qualifications and thanked outgoing Chairman Joseph Dunford for his service. The President also highlighted the strength and capabilities of the American military, including the successful defeat of ISIS and the rebuilding of the military under his administration. He emphasized the importance of military families and expressed gratitude to Gold Star families and veterans in attendance. The President also mentioned the creation of the Space Force as a significant achievement. The article concludes with the President expressing confidence in General Milley's ability to fulfill his duties and a commitment to keeping America safe and proud.